rohibited. Also, source stubs in the org.osgi package aren’t allowed. One idea could be adding a dependency for actual OSGi and running Felix. That might allow me to load HV into the OSGi framework. It's a thought worth exploring since it could help me work around the restrictions I'm facing! I'll need to test this approach further.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Writing test for message interpolator**\\n\\nI need to write a test for the ResourceBundleMessageInterpolator. There are existing tests in the org.hibernate.validator package, but the rules specify that I should keep the dynamic class in its own test file. So, I’ll create a new test file named `com.example.hibernatevalidator.ResourceBundleMessageInterpolatorTest`. This way, I can ensure that the tests are organized and follow the guidelines! It'll help keep everything clean and manageable.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_8q1WNhHU3Bgu16zMxeFBtK4x|fc_07128e2cacf06c13016a3bf31eff548193a8d6979caab1cda6", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "grep -R \"getUnableToInitializeELExpressionFactoryException\" -n /home/mihailo/git/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/source_context/org.hibernate.validator/hibernate-validator/9.1.0.Final/main/extracted/org/hibernate/validator/internal/util/logging/Log.java"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2933, "output": 2745, "cacheRead": 19968, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 25646, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1782313718421, "responseId": "resp_07128e2cacf06c13016a3bf2f7032081939bc0896ac18b09e7"}}
