s5tLjoex43gK3E96l-WbKakadCGHqcTlf0QGbF_ZMFNjp6ydOS7Mch9xNdE1racOsEK-dO7Pz4zj3WgjICOhmuXTEfqCFVjkzspkDvMdwr0_C40WG_YX2zNI79y-AeWTYSkiANjmiW1IG6AkJzhW0k0-a5TS1bb_ib5evPhEpZqUxD5Q9LT2d_mlkLdjJAD5ZLRpzsYvGAF0uXOc2aUSDNnd1k5T2gNi6-B52eKWWODQnyE=\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating service configuration**\\n\\nI’m realizing that ServiceConfigurationError extends Error, so when ExpressionFactory.newInstance throws an Error, the canLoad method catches Throwable, returning false. This could cause issues for positive tests since it would make all EL lookups fail unless we skip adding the resource. Maybe we could create a conditional ThrowingExpressionFactory constructor based on a system property. If the property is set to \\\"disable,\\\" it would throw; otherwise, it would delegate to the provider. However, I’m concerned about compatibility with existing tests and dependencies.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring service provider options**\\n\\nI see that without an alternative conditional service provider, we're facing limitations for the test. One option could be to use a resource service that only throws an error when a specific property is set; otherwise, it delegates calls by using `ExpressionFactory.newInstance()`, which might end up recursing. I’m wondering if it’s possible to instantiate a fallback class by name, and for Expressly 6, it’s likely `org.glassfish.expressly.ExpressionFactoryImpl`. Maybe searching the documentation could help clarify this!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Troubleshooting framework issues**\\n\\nIt looks like I've encountered an issue where `FrameworkUtil.getBundle` is returning null, which is important to address. I need to create a specific resource file, `src/test/resources/META-INF/services/jakarta.el.ExpressionFactory`, with the correct nested service binary name. I also realize that the top-level test class should include a public static final class, `SwitchableExpressionFactory`. This will help manage the expression factories properly.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_LGI0ItHPJd2kdpaErf39Bn6e|fc_07128e2cacf06c13016a3bf43098c08193b6c92e34a3a8c1c3", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "python3 - <<'PY'\nimport urllib.request, zipfile, io\nurl='https://repo.maven.apache.org/maven2/org/glassfish/expressly/expressly/6.0.0/expressly-6.0.0-sources.jar'\ndata=urllib.request.urlopen(url, timeout=15).read()\nz=zipfile.ZipFile(io.BytesIO(data))\nfor n in z.namelist():\n    if n.endswith('ExpressionFactoryImpl.java'):\n        print(n)\nPY", "timeout": 20}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 771, "output": 1375, "cacheRead": 31744, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 33890, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1782314010556, "responseId": "resp_07128e2cacf06c13016a3bf41b65788193a2e7a564ce4b7c17"}}
