hind this branch in `ResourceBundleMessageInterpolator.classLoaderForExpressionFactory()`:\n\n```java\nObject currentBundle = getBundle.invoke(null, ResourceBundleMessageInterpolator.class);\nif (currentBundle != null) {\n    Object context = cl.loadClass(\"org.osgi.framework.Bundle\")\n            .getMethod(\"getBundleContext\")\n            .invoke(currentBundle);\n    Object bundles = cl.loadClass(\"org.osgi.framework.BundleContext\")\n            .getMethod(\"getBundles\")\n            .invoke(context);\n    Method loadClass = cl.loadClass(\"org.osgi.framework.Bundle\")\n            .getMethod(\"loadClass\", String.class);\n    ...\n}\n```\n\nThe already-added test reaches the supported Java SE fallback far enough to cover:\n\n- `ClassLoader.loadClass(\"org.osgi.framework.FrameworkUtil\")`\n- `FrameworkUtil.getMethod(\"getBundle\", Class.class)`\n- `getBundle.invoke(...)`\n\nThe remaining sites require `FrameworkUtil.getBundle(ResourceBundleMessageInterpolator.class)` to return a non-null OSGi `Bundle`. With the normal Gradle/JUnit test classpath, Hibernate Validator is loaded by the application class loader, so real OSGi `FrameworkUtil` correctly returns `null`.\n\nCovering the rest would require loading Hibernate Validator from an OSGi bundle/class loader or using a fake/shadowed OSGi API. Both are disallowed here:\n\n- OSGi class loader paths are explicitly excluded by the task rules.\n- Source stubs/shadow classes in dependency packages are explicitly prohibited.\n- Direct reflection into Hibernate Validator’s private method is prohibited.\n\nSo the remaining 9 dynamic-access sites should stay uncovered for this class with that explanation. The public Jakarta Validation bootstrap path remains covered, including the reporter-requested JBoss Logging initialization path.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_07128e2cacf06c13016a3bf67ef85c819395d5469b6c4461f7\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5